AVIAN INFLUENZA, HUMAN (83): VIET NAM (NGHE AN) H5N6
****************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Sun 5 Apr 2015
Source: Avian Flu Diary [edited]
http://afludiary.blogspot.com


Avian Flu Diary has published an on-line report picked up from several news sources in Viet Nam of 2 people infected with the recently emerged A/H5N6 avian virus in Nghe An Province. Dr. Michael Coston, [editor, Avian Flu Diary] feels the report is accurate, as just over 2 weeks ago, the virus was reported in the adjacent province to the north (see comment below).

An outbreak of avian influenza A / H5N6 outbreak in Quy Hop district, Nghe An, caused an infection in 2 people. The Local Veterinary Authority has issued 11 000 doses of vaccine to control the outbreak. The source Pioneer said outbreaks of avian influenza occurred in the neighborhood of Dinh Xuan Nghia, Quy Hop district, Nghe An. It is a location with concentrated population.

Talking to reporters from dimension 5/4, the Director of DARD in Nghe An, Ho Ngoc Sy, confirmed the report, adding that after the outbreak, the veterinary authorities in collaboration with the district of Nghe implemented advanced emergency measures [in the rural district of Quy Hop] to control and extinguish the outbreak.

"There are families raising chickens, 150 children in [contact with?] infected chickens. The province has mobilized 11 000 doses of vaccine against the disease and will conduct quarantine and disinfection of the whole barn area that has bird flu. They have temporarily banned the sale of poultry in the affected area," said Ho Ngoc Sy.

The Director of Health Services in Nghe An, Long Bui Dinh, said the 2 patients infected with avian influenza A / H5N6 were transferred to Hanoi for treatment.

In early August 2014, H5N6 suddenly popped up in widely separated outbreaks in central and northern Vietnam (see http://afludiary.blogspot.com/2014/08/oie-two-outbreaks-of-h5n6-in-vietnamese.html), hundreds of kilometers south of its original emergence. Since then there have been at least 6 additional reports of outbreaks in Vietnamese poultry.

Over the past few months China has reported more than 2 dozen outbreaks around the country (see OIE, http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public%5C..%5Ctemp%5Creports/en_fup_0000017459_20150403_145032.pdf), and 2 days ago, Fri 3 Apr 2015, FluTrackers reported an unconfirmed case from China: "Farmer suspected H5N6 bird flu case after outbreak in geese," in Wujin District, Changzhou City, Jiangsu Province, China. (https://flutrackers.com/forum/forum/china-h5n1-h5n8-h5n6-h5n3-h5n2-h10n8-outbreak-tracking/728618-china-farmer-suspected-h5n6-bird-flu-case-after-outbreak-in-geese-april-3-2015).

